a radius of [`r_A=[$ra]\:m`], and disk [`B`] as a mass of [`m_B=[$mb]\:kg`] and radius of [`r_B=[$rb]\:m`], find the angular velocity of disk [`A`]
after it has rotated [`[$rev]`] revolutions. If the balloon has a mass of [`m_{balloon}=[$mball]\:kg`], and the tension in the cable after [`[$rev]`] revolutions
is [`T=[$T]\:N`], find the upward force of the balloon at that instant.

[`{\omega}_A = `][_____]{"$omegaa"}[`rad/s`]

[`F_{balloon} = `][_____]{"$Fb"}[`N`]

END_PGML

